## PolyAsyncIterable.append() method

Return a new iteration that will iterate over `this`<!-- -->, then over `other`<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
append<U>(other: Iterable<U> | AsyncIterable<U>): PolyAsyncIterable<T | U>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  other | Iterable&lt;U&gt; \| AsyncIterable&lt;U&gt; | Iterable to be appended |

<b>Returns:</b>

PolyAsyncIterable&lt;T \| U&gt;

a new [PolyAsyncIterable](./polyethylene.polyasynciterable.md) that yields the elements of `this` and then the elements of `other`

## Remarks

The resulting iteration is of the combined generic type of `this` and `other`<!-- -->, allowing this method to merge the types of two distinct iterables.
